Have you noticed anything strange between her and the president?

548
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,330
什么意思
How do you mean?

549
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:08,560
昨天我在走道里碰见他们
I passed them in the hall yesterday.

550
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:13,010
他们看上去  我说不好  很亲密
And they seem -- I don't know -- very intimate.

551
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:15,870
预备会议上他们是挺热络的
They did seem cozy at the prep session.

552
00:27:17,340 --> 00:27:18,440
你觉得...
Do you think...?

553
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:21,260
不  不一定
No. Not necessarily.

554
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:23,720
不过这想法挺有意思
An interesting thought, though.

555
00:27:24,020 --> 00:27:24,960
抱歉打扰  先生
Sorry to interrupt, sir.

556
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,020
我们在吃午饭
We're having lunch.

557
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:27,410
共和党人变卦了
The Republicans are backing out.

558
00:27:27,410 --> 00:27:29,250
门多萨的幕僚长给我提了醒
Mendoza's chief of staff just gave me the heads-up.

559
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,660
马上帮我接门多萨
Get Mendoza on the phone.

560
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:33,410
是柯蒂斯·哈斯  他临阵退缩了
It's Curtis Haas. He got cold feet.

561
00:27:34,150 --> 00:27:37,770
笼子  差不多像那样  不过
Cages. It's really kinda like but,

562
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:40,340
但大家会看  挺逗的
you know, people look at 'em. It's kind of fun.

563
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,050
我收到你邮件了
I got your email.

564
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:43,000
你现在有空吗
Now good for you?

565
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,480
当然  我过会儿打给你
Yeah, sure. Can I call you right back?

566
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,550
你究竟想问什么
What exactly did you need to know?

567
00:27:48,790 --> 00:27:51,250
我们在做网络战的后续报道
We're doing some follow-up pieces on the cyber warfare thing.

568
00:27:51,250 --> 00:27:53,230
我就想问问内行人知不知道
I just wanted to get a layman's understanding

569
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:56,010
中国人会如何越过防火墙
of how the Chinese might get through a firewall.

570
00:27:56,140 --> 00:27:58,470
挺复杂的  不过我可以演示下基本原理
It's a bit complicated, but I could show you the basics.

571
00:27:58,470 --> 00:27:59,840
那足够了
That's all I need.

572
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:19,020
我们使用的是标准多层体系结构
We use a standard N-tier architecture.

573
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:21,680
就像多层面包做成的大三明治
Think of it like a big sandwich with layers of bread.

574
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:26,000
每层之间夹着生菜  番茄  烤牛肉之类的
Between each is the lettuce, the tomato, the roast beef, whatever.

575
00:28:26,710 --> 00:28:28,410
我现在输入的是组织代码
What I'm pulling up here is the org code,

576
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:30,160
隔离了数据库
which, uh, separates the database --

577
